rawn from therapy, as there may be a significant risk of adrenal suppression. Signs and symptoms of adrenal insufficiency include anorexia, hypoglycemia, nausea, vomiting, weight loss, muscle wasting, fatigue, weakness, dizziness, postural hypotension, depression, and adrenal crisis manifested as inability to respond to stress (e.g., illness, infection, surgery, trauma).', 'Metabolism', 'Concomitant use of budesonide with potent CYP450 3A4 inhibitors should generally be avoided.', 'Major', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/50142/', '', 'Paritaprevir, Glecaprevir, Tenofovir alafenamide, Maraviroc, Simeprevir, Cabotegravir, Zanamivir, Velpatasvir, Rilpivirine, Dolutegravir, Brincidofovir, More', 'Mometasone furoate, Terbutaline, Umeclidinium, Aclidinium, Glycopyrronium, Epinephrine, Olodaterol, Cromoglicic acid, Ipratropium, Orciprenaline, Pirbuterol, More', 1767369485);
